snippet: The woman was said to be in serious condition with head injuries from the accident, which happened near the West 86th Street park entrance.
abstract: Tourist is seriously injured when she is struck by a falling tree branch in Central Park while walking with her husband; previous injuries and deaths from falling limbs have raised questions about whether New York City is doing enough to keep people safe from falling branches.

byline.original: By JOSEPH GOLDSTEIN and RANDY LEONARD

lead_paragraph: The woman was said to be in serious condition with head injuries from the accident, which happened near the West 86th Street park entrance.

headline.seo: Branch Falls on Tourist as She Walks Through Central Park
